title: Nuevos Destinos (2001)
description:
Nuevos Destinos
	 

A multimedia instructional series in Spanish for college and high school classrooms and adult learners; 15 video programs (12 to 19 minutes in length), and coordinated books

The multimedia Nuevos Destinos expands the ways you can use the original Destinos story. Retelling the story of lawyer Raquel RodrÃƒÂ­guez's original investigation within the framework of a new legal intrigue, Nuevos Destinos is designed for courses in which less video and a specific pedagogical focus are needed.

These materials are useful for students in all of the following: intensive review and high beginner courses; intermediate grammar review courses; and intermediate courses in conversation and composition.

Produced by WGBH Boston with McGraw-Hill. 2001.
